"A man enjoys the happiness he feels, and a woman the happiness she gives.\n\n- A.J.  Rich, The Hand That Feeds You\n|\nThe grave's a fine and private place,But none, I think, do there embrace.\n\n- Andrew Marvell, To His Coy Mistress\n|\nIf you are faithful in little things, then you will be given a bigger commitment.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nWhen we fall in love, we recognise in the other the fragments of ourselves that we have lost.\n\n- Dragos Bratasanu, Ph.D.\n|\nLife is not others' perception about you, but what you experience within.\n\n- quotewriter\n|\nEvery challenge you encounter in life is a fork in the road. You have the choice to choose which way to go - backward, forward, breakdown or breakthrough.\n\n- Ifeanyi Enoch Onuoha, Overcoming the Challenges of Life\n|\nI work hard, I work very hard. All the books at least 30 revisions.\n\n- Ha\n|\nDusty, dark, cold, and hard, coal has no beauty of its own, but when it is consummated by fire it is beautiful and becomes what it was designed to be.\n\n- Frederica Mathewes-Green, At the Corner of East and Now: A Modern Life in Ancient Christian Orthodoxy\n|\nSometimes to love people, I must completely avoid them. Sometimes, to be strong, I must completely fall apart. Sometimes, to create, I must completely destroy.\n\n- Vironika\n|\nIn the Book of Life, The answers aren't in the back.\n\n- Charles\n|\nFor there comes a day on which we will see a mirror of judgement; to gaze not on man, but within ourselves. what cometh on that day in you? truth or despair? love or hate?\n\n- Robert\n|\nLook in my face; my name is Might-have-been; I am also call'd No-more, Too-late, Farewell\n\n- Dante Gabriel Rossetti, The House of Life\n|\nLove [is] supposed to move mountains, to make the world go round, to be all you need, but it [falls] apart at the deatils. It [can't] save a single person.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, Nineteen Minutes\n|\nIgnorance causes pain, but awareness creates happiness. Therefore, look for enlightenment every day.\n\n- Linda Alfiori, The Art of Loving Intelligently: Discover the Five Love Myths Hurting Women Worldwide and the Reality about Them\n|\nAs we began discussing authorship of a white paper summarizing our conclusions, we debated who our target audience should be and what kind of outcome we were hoping to achieve.\n\n- Jennifer A. Doudna, A Crack in Creation: Gene Editing and the Unthinkable Power to Control Evolution\n|\nLike poetry, fashion does not state anything. It merely suggests\n\n- Karl\n|\nA slip of the foot may injure your body, but a slip of the tongue will injure your bond.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nThe truth is seldom welcome, especially at dinner.\n\n- Margaret Atwood, Morning in the Burned House\n|\nHappiness is a strange, frightening, fragile feeling when you're not used to it.\n\n- Amanda Bouchet, A Promise of Fire\n|\nThere is no present or future-only the past, happening over and over again-now.\n\n- Eugene O'Neill, A Moon for the Misbegotten\n|\nPainful as it may be, a significant emotional event can be the catalyst for choosing a direction that serves us - and those around us - more effectively. Look for the learning.\n\n- Louisa\n|\nThere is mighty force, energy, ability inside of us that has not yet been noticed by the world\n\n- Sunday\n|\nMy God had not spoken to me again. But neither had He forsaken me. I knew that. For damned sure, I knew that.\n\n- Marcus\n|\nIt’s important to take God’s love personally, though it may not be an easy thing to do. Sure, God loves the world, but he also loves each one of us individually.\n\n- Tim Tebow, Shaken: Discovering Your True Identity in the Midst of Life's Storms\n|\nI do not say words, which you want to hear.The words just told me, to write them down.\n\n- Toba\n|\nWe’re only instruments of love, flowing through heaps of pain hoping one day we’d hatch a passion of our own.\n\n- Robert\n|\nYour life may not have gone the way you planned it, but it will go the way it's supposed to.\n\n- Jeanette\n|\nAre there any other missing persons living under your roof? Elvis? Jimmy Hoffa? Amelia Earhart? I'd just like full disclosure now, before we go any further.\n\n- Maggie Stiefvater, Forever\n|\nA song is the exultation of the mind dwelling on eternal things, bursting forth in the voice.\n\n- Thomas\n|\nThe law of sacrifice postulates that we need to give in order to receive ... Cosmic Ordering says, receive before you give.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering: You can be successful\n|\nYou're either living on purpose or living accidentally, so live ON purpose WITH purpose!\n\n- Ken Donaldson, Marry YourSelf First! Companion Workbook\n|\nIn the life of every Christian, there is a wilderness experience\n\n- Sunday\n|\nLife has taught me that money is important, but it's not everything. For, if I have all the money in the world, but no time to enjoy, of what use is it?\n\n- RVM\n|\nWhenever you read a good book, somewhere in the world a door opens to allow in more light.\n\n- Vera\n|\nOpportunities will never notify you before knocking, but you need to be ready to open the doors.\n\n- Damini Aggarwal, Zindagi Rewind\n|\nYou can't just plan a moment when things get back on track, just as you can't plan the moment you lose your way in the first place.\n\n- Sarah Dessen, Someone Like You\n|\nYesterday I was clever,That is why I wanted to change the world.Today I am wise,That is why I am changing myself.\n\n- Sri Chinmoy, The Wings of Joy: Finding Your Path to Inner Peace\n|\nEverything in life has some good in it. And when something awful happens, the goodness stands out even more--it's sad, but that's the truth.\n\n- Banana Yoshimoto, The Lake\n|\nBuddha had said:'Each of us is a God. Each of us knows all. We need only open our minds to hear our own wisdom.\n\n- Dan Brown, Angels & Demons\n|\nShe stabbed him with her wicked pretty knife, disrupted his simple life.She's a player, a heartbreaker,and now she breaks alone.\n\n- Coco\n|\nIf many good things have not happened in your life, God is not to be blamed\n\n- Sunday\n|\nIn my view, nineteen pounds of old books are at least nineteen times as delicious as one pound of fresh caviar.\n\n- Anne Fadiman, Ex Libris: Confessions of a Common Reader\n|\nDivorce lawyers stoke anger and fear in their clients, knowing that as long as the conflicts remain unresolved the revenue stream will keep flowing.\n\n- Craig Ferguson, American on Purpose: The Improbable Adventures of an Unlikely Patriot\n|\nRemember that a wish held fervently turns into belief, and a belief held diligently becomes reality.\n\n- Jim Stovall, The Lamp\n|\nDon't just Hurry, don't just Haste. Don't just Worry, don't just Waste. Life is a Treasure, Enjoy the Pleasure.\n\n- RVM\n|\nWhat a strange creature is a laughing fool,As if a man were created to no useBut only to show his teeth.\n\n- John Webster, The White Devil\n|\nA poet must discover that it’s his own story that is true, even if the truth is small indeed.\n\n- Jim\n|\n(About sweeping)....What he was in FACT doing was moving the dirt around with a broom, to give it a change of scenery and a chance to make new friends.\n\n- Terry Pratchett, Maskerade\n|\nOur ultimate finishing line in life is death! Whilst you have life, work hard and trust God!\n\n- Ernest\n|\nComing up with a useful, meaningful quote is getting more and more challenging each day....and you can quote me on that.\n\n- Bobby Darnell, Time For Dervin - Living Large In Geiggityville\n|\nThe more a book is like an opium pipe, the more the Chinaman reader is satisfied with it and tends to discuss the quality of the drug rather than its lethargic effects.\n\n- Julio Cortázar, Around the Day in Eighty Worlds\n|\nWhen you can only remember the mundane things you did but do not have any valuable products to show for your time, then you are a time spender.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nIn real life, love has to be possible. Even if it is not returned right away, love can only survive when the hope exists that you will be able to win over the person you desire.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, By the River Piedra I Sat Down and Wept\n|\nAnytime, someone gives you advice, rethink if it will lead to personal progress.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nThe Universe is not only queerer than we suppose, but queerer than we can suppose.\n\n- J.B.S. Haldane, Possible Worlds\n|\nAn average man is egoistic, proud and has strong self esteem. They always require partners who massage their ego not those who will drag their ego to the mud.\n\n- Jaachynma\n|\nScience ask facts and religion ask faith, humans are confused between life and death.\n\n- Santosh\n|\nA Rule: Life without Islam is a naked tree,Birds without trees can never feel free.\n\n- Leena Ahmad Almashat, Harmony Letters\n|\nThe best way to succeed is to have a specific Intent, a clear Vision, a plan of Action, and the ability to maintain Clarity. Those are the Four Pillars of Success. It never fails!\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Life, the Truth, and Being Free\n|\nPain was good. If I hurt, it meant I wasn't dead.\n\n- Kristin Cast, Hunted\n|\nTo escape fear, you have to go through it, not around.\n\n- Richie Norton, Résumés Are Dead and What to Do About It\n|\nIn a totally sane society, madness is the only freedom.\n\n- J.G. Ballard, Running Wild\n|\nBe an example to teach, be a role model to follow, and be a leader to emulate.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nCommunication succeeds when you make others understand you clearly, and they make you understand them clearly.\n\n- Nabil\n|\nTo me you are a work of art, and I would give you my heart - that's if I had one.\n\n- Morrissey\n|\nEmpathy is easier than anger, in the long-run.\n\n- Sam Owen, 500 Relationships And Life Quotes: Bite-Sized Advice For Busy People\n|\nSometimes, you simply must give yourself permission to fall apart.\n\n- Mishi\n|\nWhen you choose your friends, don't be short-changed by choosing personality over character.\n\n- W.\n|\nD'autant que nous avons cher, estre, et estre consiste en mouvement et action.\n\n- Michel de Montaigne, The Complete Essays\n|\nDo your thoughts continue and repeat a cycle Seed, growth, bloom, and seed again\n\n- Richard\n|\nIf there's one thing I've learned, it's that God is a very creative author, and He writes a different story for every person. No two lives or stories alike.\n\n- Robin Jones Gunn, With This Ring\n|\nBy the very act of arguing, you awake the patient's reason; and once it is awake, who can foresee the result?\n\n- C.S.\n|\nDemocracy arose from men's thinking that if they are equal in any respect, they are equal absolutely.\n\n- Aristotle\n|\nLove is everything a person desires for in his life, but love is not in getting love, but giving the most love you have to others\n\n- Shaikh Ashraf, Friendship, Love & Sacrifice\n|\nNever allow your life to be dictated by what you can see by sight, be guided by your inner vision.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nWisdom is when you understand what, previously, at best you only knew.\n\n- Idries Shah, Observations\n|\nYou can't eat hope,' the woman said.You can't eat it, but it sustains you,' the colonel replied.\n\n- Gabriel García Márquez, El coronel no tiene quien le escriba\n|\nWill be but corpses dressed in frocks, who cannot speak to birds or rocks.\n\n- Gary\n|\nTo everyone who gets me, thank you. To everyone who doesn't, thank you too. You give me the motivation to keep succeeding just to piss you off.\n\n- Shane Dawson, It Gets Worse: A Collection of Essays\n|\nPeople stumble over the truth from time to time,but most pick themselves up and hurry off as if nothing happened.\n\n- Winston\n|\nTake caution when declaring war because you may believe it will be easy, but war will always end in despair.\n\n- Anonymous\n|\nIt doesn't matter who you are, or where you come from, or how much money you've got in your pocket. You have your own destiny and your own life ahead of you.\n\n- Lady\n|\nYou'll forget it when you're dead, and so will I. When I'm dead, I'm going to forget everything–and I advise you to do the same.\n\n- Kurt Vonnegut Jr., Cat's Cradle\n|\nBut in that moment I understood what they say about nostalgia, that no matter if you're thinking of something good or bad, it always leaves you a little emptier afterward.\n\n- John Corey Whaley, Noggin\n|\nKeep me away from the wisdom which does not cry, the philosophy which does not laugh and the greatness which does not bow before children.\n\n- Kahlil Gibran, Mirrors of the Soul\n|\nThanks to you my toughest life lessons.. it may appear that I'm falling, ... but, I' m stronger than I have ever been\n\n- Virginia\n|\nMardi Gras, baby. Mardi Gras. Time when all manner of weird shit cuts loose and parties down.\n\n- Sherrilyn Kenyon, No Mercy\n|\nSome birds are not meant to be caged, that's all. Their feathers are too bright, their songs too sweet and wild.\n\n- Stephen King, Rita Hayworth and Shawshank Redemption: A Story from Different Seasons\n|\nThought is so cunning, so clever, that it distorts everything for its own convenience.\n\n- Jiddu Krishnamurti, Freedom from the Known\n|\nYes - en I's rich now, come to look at it. I owns myself, en I's wuth eight hund'd dollars. I wisht I had de money, I wouldn' want no mo'.\n\n- Mark Twain, The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn\n|\nSo many broken promises, each day an aborted wish, a lost object, a misplaced unread book, cluttering the room like an attic with discarded possessions.\n\n- Anaïs Nin, The Four-Chambered Heart: V3 in Nin's Continuous Novel\n|\nSo because you are converting it, you are actually conserving it.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nMind is effort, while heart is effortless! What are YOU?\n\n- Ramana\n|\nPure intuitive faith differs as much from fanaticism as fire from smoke, or music from mere noise; those who confuse the two are like the deaf.\n\n- José\n|\nNeither were you [born yesterday], unless of course I am wrong, in which case welcome to the world, little baby, and congratulations on learning to read so early in life.\n\n- Lemony Snicket, The Penultimate Peril\n|\nDo the best you can, with what you can, while you can, and success in inevitable.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Unapologetically You: Reflections on Life and the Human Experience\n|\nIf it's knowledge and wisdom you want, then seek out the company of those who do real work for an honest purpose.\n\n- Edward Abbey, Postcards from Ed: Dispatches and Salvos from an American Iconoclast\n|\nDEAR LIGHT : you colored my life, and then you destroy me!\n\n- Vergi\n|\nWhat Youth deemed crystal, Age finds out was dew\n\n- Robert Browning, Jocoseria\n|\nWe must be free not because we claim freedom, but because we practice it.\n\n- William Faulkner, Essays, Speeches & Public Letters"